    {
      "id": "/page/1/TextInlineMath/9",
      "block_type": "TextInlineMath",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"TextInlineMath\">The parallels of equation <math display=\"inline\">(1)</math> to the valuation of contingent claims in default-free interest rate term structure models also extend to the methodology of Heath et al. [10] (HJM). Defining a term structure of \"defaultable instantaneous forward rates\" <math display=\"inline\">\\bar{f}(t, T)</math> in terms of defaultable zero-coupon bond prices <math display=\"inline\">\\bar{B}(t,T)</math>(i.e., the time <math display=\"inline\">t</math> price of a bond maturing in <math display=\"inline\">T</math>) by</p>",
