    {
      "id": "/page/1/Text/16",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">Cast in terms of HJM, the model is automatically calibrated to an initial term structure of defaultable discount factors <math display=\"inline\">\\bar{B}(t, T)</math>. This type of straightforward \"cross-sectional\" calibration makes the model useful not only for the econometric estimation followed by Duffie and Singleton [8] and others such as Duffee [4] and Collin-Dufresne and Solnik [1] but also for the relative pricing of credit derivatives.</p>",
